[The Northland Region is the northernmost of New Zealand's 16 local government regions. New Zealanders often call it the Far North, or, because of its mild climate, the Winterless North. The main population centre is the city of Whangarei and the largest town is Kerikeri https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northland_Region.

_Mycoplasma bovis_ is on the north of the northern island. This disease now seems to have reached almost the entire country, as cases are found on both islands. - Mod.TG

